t it into\na long tibble with columns `(chr, start, end, strand, metric, value, sample)` using\n`pivot_longer` on the `coverage*`/`numCs*` columns, and save it to\n`output/df_mku.rds`. Then pivot wide on `metric`, compute `mCpG = numCs / coverage`,\ngroup by `(sample, chr)`, and write the mean mCpG table to `output/mean_mcpg.tsv`\nusing `readr::write_tsv` with columns `sample, chr, mean_mCpG`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mean_mcpg.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_db\": {\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"methylBase_unite.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleA.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleB.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleC.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz\"\n      },\n      \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\": {\n        \"_file\": \"sampleD.txt.bgz.tbi\"\n      }\n    },\n    \"mk_united.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_united.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mean_mcpg.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_kwWaWLRKZSPyJPQSObbAOvBS", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the methylKit united object from 'input/mk_united.rds'.\\n2. Convert the methylKit object into a long tibble with columns (chr, start, end, strand, metric, value, sample) using pivot_longer.\\n3. Save the long tibble to 'output/df_mku.rds'.\\n4. Pivot the tibble wide on 'metric' and compute mCpG = numCs / coverage.\\n5. Group the data by (sample, chr) and calculate the mean mCpG.\\n6. Write the mean mCpG table to 'output/mean_mcpg.tsv' using readr::write_tsv.\\n7. Verify the existence of 'output/mean_mcpg.tsv' and submit the task as done.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (540 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_kwWaWLRKZSPyJPQSObbAOvBS"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_IEjHim8GTnbt1I4rp8gyo6Fp", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(readr)\\nlibrary(tibble)\\n\\n# Load the methylKit united object\\nmk_united <- readRDS('input/mk_united.rds')\\n\\n# Convert to tibble\\nmku_df <- as.data.frame(mk_united) %>%\\n  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with('coverage') | starts_with('numCs'),\\n               names_to = 'metric', values_to = 'value') %>%\\n  mutate(sample = sub('.*_', '', metric),\\n         metric = sub('_.*', '', metric)) %>%\\n  select(chr, start, end, strand, metric, value, sample)\\n\\n# Save the long tibble\\nsaveRDS(mku_df, 'output/df_mku.rds')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role":